tafsir[12]{c,v,t}:
  51,7,"By heaven with all its tracks"
  51,9,"and perverted therefrom are some."
  51,10,"Perish the conjecturers"
  51,11,"who are dazed in perplexity"
  51,13,"Upon the day when they shall be tried at the Fire:"
  51,14,"'Taste your trial! This is that you were seeking to hasten.'"
  51,15,"Surely the godfearing shall be among gardens and fountains"
  51,16,"taking whatsoever their Lord has given them; they were good-doers before that."
  51,18,"and in the mornings they would ask for forgiveness;"
  51,19,"and the beggar and the outcast had a share in their wealth."
  51,20,"In the earth are signs for those having sure faith;"
  51,24,"Hast thou received the story of the honoured guests of Abraham?"